<font face=Arial,Helvetica>
<b>Some Republicans questioning War on Drugs</b><br><font face=Arial,Helvetica size=1>Posted on  Wednesday, August 02 @ 09:58:29 EDT

</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td bgcolor=ffffff>
<font face=Arial,Helvetica>
<a href=search.php3?query=&topic=17&author=><img src=images/topics/drugs.jpg border=0 Alt="War on Drugs" align=right hspace=10 vspace=10></a>
<P><A href="http://www.wirednews.com/news/politics/0,1283,37933,00.html">This Wired News article</A> suggests that a growing number of Republicans are calling for an end to the War on Drugs.  I wish the mainstream media would cover this angle, but I'm not holding my breath.</P>

<P>There seems to be growing discontent with the drug war from all over the political spectrum.  We obviously haven't won the War Against the War on Drugs yet, but an end to Prohibition seems almost inevitable at this point.  Or am I just overly optimistic?</P> 
</td>
</tr>
